Document: Sprite2D
Path: godot/classes/class_sprite2d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the Sprite2D node in Godot Engine.

Property: centered
Type: bool
Default: true
Description: If true, texture is centered.
Note: For games with a pixel art aesthetic, textures may appear deformed when centered. This is caused by their position being between pixels. To prevent this, set this property to false, or consider enabling ProjectSettings.rendering/2d/snap/snap_2d_vertices_to_pixel and ProjectSettings.rendering/2d/snap/snap_2d_transforms_to_pixel.
Method: set_centered(value: bool)
Method: is_centered() -> bool

Property: flip_h
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, texture is flipped horizontally.
Method: set_flip_h(value: bool)
Method: is_flipped_h() -> bool

Property: flip_v
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, texture is flipped vertically.
Method: set_flip_v(value: bool)
Method: is_flipped_v() -> bool

Property: frame
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: Current frame to display from sprite sheet. hframes or vframes must be greater than 1. This property is automatically adjusted when hframes or vframes are changed to keep pointing to the same visual frame (same column and row). If that's impossible, this value is reset to 0.
Method: set_frame(value: int)
Method: get_frame() -> int

Property: frame_coords
Type: Vector2i
Default: Vector2i(0, 0)
Description: Coordinates of the frame to display from sprite sheet. This is as an alias for the frame property. hframes or vframes must be greater than 1.
Method: set_frame_coords(value: Vector2i)
Method: get_frame_coords() -> Vector2i

Property: hframes
Type: int
Default: 1
Description: The number of columns in the sprite sheet. When this property is changed, frame is adjusted so that the same visual frame is maintained (same row and column). If that's impossible, frame is reset to 0.
Method: set_hframes(value: int)
Method: get_hframes() -> int

Property: offset
Type: Vector2
Default: Vector2(0, 0)
Description: The texture's drawing offset.
Note: When you increase offset.y in Sprite2D, the sprite moves downward on screen (i.e., +Y is down).
Method: set_offset(value: Vector2)
Method: get_offset() -> Vector2

Property: region_enabled
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, texture is cut from a larger atlas texture. See region_rect.
Note: When using a custom Shader on a Sprite2D, the UV shader built-in will refer to the entire texture space. Use the REGION_RECT built-in to get the currently visible region defined in region_rect instead. See CanvasItem shaders for details.
Method: set_region_enabled(value: bool)
Method: is_region_enabled() -> bool

Property: region_filter_clip_enabled
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, the area outside of the region_rect is clipped to avoid bleeding of the surrounding texture pixels. region_enabled must be true.
Method: set_region_filter_clip_enabled(value: bool)
Method: is_region_filter_clip_enabled() -> bool

Property: region_rect
Type: Rect2
Default: Rect2(0, 0, 0, 0)
Description: The region of the atlas texture to display. region_enabled must be true.
Method: set_region_rect(value: Rect2)
Method: get_region_rect() -> Rect2

Property: texture
Type: Texture2D
Description: Texture2D object to draw.
Method: set_texture(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture() -> Texture2D

Property: vframes
Type: int
Default: 1
Description: The number of rows in the sprite sheet. When this property is changed, frame is adjusted so that the same visual frame is maintained (same row and column). If that's impossible, frame is reset to 0.
Method: set_vframes(value: int)
Method: get_vframes() -> int
---CHUNK---
Document: Sprite2D
Path: godot/classes/class_sprite2d.rst
Summary: Provides descriptions for the Sprite2D class methods get_rect and is_pixel_opaque.
Method: get_rect() → Rect2
Returns a Rect2 representing the Sprite2D's boundary in local coordinates.

Example: Detect if the Sprite2D was clicked:

GDScript:
func _input(event):
    if event is InputEventMouseButton and event.pressed and event.button_index == MOUSE_BUTTON_LEFT:
        if get_rect().has_point(to_local(event.position)):
            print("A click!")

C#:
public override void _Input(InputEvent @event)
{
    if (@event is InputEventMouseButton inputEventMouse)
    {
        if (inputEventMouse.Pressed && inputEventMouse.ButtonIndex == MouseButton.Left)
        {
            if (GetRect().HasPoint(ToLocal(inputEventMouse.Position)))
            {
                GD.Print("A click!");
            }
        }
    }
}

Method: is_pixel_opaque(pos: Vector2) → bool
Returns true if the pixel at the given position is opaque, false otherwise. Also returns false if the given position is out of bounds or this sprite's texture is null. pos is in local coordinates.